RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRABIESO AVELITO tracked the pacesetter for five furlongs, was roused two then three wide to the stretch, closed in a rally and was along in time. PIVOTAL FEVER went right to the front, set the pace to the far turn, was set down for the drive but could not stall the winner. LOOKOUT POINT chased the pace from the rail to the stretch then was making progress inside to the wire. MR BOTANICALS hopped in the air at the start and lost a bout five lengths, trailed for half mile, was fanned four wide while attempting to rally on the far turn but flattened out in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Pivotal Fever
ENTRY.COMMENT: cleaar lead, set down, battled, tagged

ENTRY.NAME: Trabieso Avelito
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leader, roused 2-3wide, rallied stretch, in time

ENTRY.NAME: Lookout Point
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace, saved ground, steady rail run

ENTRY.NAME: Mr Botanicals
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start, trailed, fanned 4wide, flattened out

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DUMB LUCK hustled early and eased inside to set the pace from the rail for a half mile, responded when challenged, edged away to mid stretch and held driving. MASTER RECOVERY was outsprinted early, bid three wide to the stretch and closed willingly for the place. SPEEDY TOM attended the pace outside the winner, was two wide then got outkicked and weakened. BEING A BOSS chased the winner for three furlongs, was fanned four wide to the stretch and lacked a closing response. FULLY LOADED had no speed and trailed.

ENTRY.NAME: Speedy Tom
ENTRY.COMMENT: attended pace, roused 2wide, outkicked, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Master Recovery
ENTRY.OWNER: Beckner Teri L and Gallus Bjorn M
ENTRY.COMMENT: outsprinted, bid 3wide, late bid 2d

ENTRY.NAME: Being a Boss
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace, fanned 4wide, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Fully Loaded
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed

ENTRY.NAME: Dumb Luck
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled, eased in, pace rail, responded, determinedly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 4 5F Dirt CR: 49. Maiden Claiming Purse 7000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAROLINE MARGARET broke a bit slow and was outsprinted to the firs turn, commended a bid after three furlongs, shifted out for room on the far turn and rallied smartly to win going away. WARNING SOUND attended the pace inside of SAINT HELEN, saved ground to the stretch then was outrun while saving second. HEAVENS TO BETSY stalked the leaders to the second turn, was two wide to the stretch and lacked the needed late response. ABBEY OOPS had no speed, saved ground to the stretch but lacked a closing response. SAINT HELEN had good speed, dueled outside a rival then inched away on the backstretch, was overtaken into the stretch then tired. A STORM TOO SOON tracked leaders, was three wide then lugged out six wide to the stretch and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: A Storm too Soon
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, lugged 6wide 2d turn, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Abbey Oops
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, saved ground, no late rally

ENTRY.NAME: Caroline Margaret
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke step slow, chased pace, shifted out, rallied, going away

ENTRY.NAME: Warning Sound
ENTRY.COMMENT: attended pace, saved ground, outkicked, saved 2d

ENTRY.NAME: Saint Helen
ENTRY.COMMENT: good speed, set pace, collared, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Heavens to Betsy
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, roused 2wide, outkicked, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY GREGORY set the pace for three furlongs, turned back bids from CAL and SPANISH CHANNEL turning for home, edged clear to mid stretch then held off SPANISH CHANNEL desperately. SPANISH CHANNEL stalked the winner for three furlongs, rallied two wide to loom boldly on the far turn, got outkicked to mid stretch but kept to task, rallied again and just missed. MO SUGAFOOT had no speed, shifted off the rail on the far turn but could not offer the needed late response. CAL pressed the pace, advanced inside to loom a threat nearing the stretch but lost her punch in the drive. LILY PAD LAKE was settled for three furlongs, closed ground three wide nearing the second turn but could not sustain that bid and tired. SHESALILRUNAWAY broke awkwardly and trailed throughout.

ENTRY.NAME: Shesalilrunaway
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke awkwardly, trailed

ENTRY.NAME: Mo Sugafoot
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, shifted off rail 2d turn, lacked needed bid

ENTRY.NAME: Lady Gregory
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, met bids 2d turn, clear, stubbornly

ENTRY.NAME: Cal
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, rail bid 2d turn, loomed, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Spanish Channel
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, rallied 2wide, loomed, outkicked, dug in, nipped

ENTRY.NAME: Lily Pad Lake
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, closed 3wide 2d turn, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY RANGER was on the pace from the outset, responded once in the stretch, dug in determinedly and got the nod. STEEL NERVES was never far back, got fanned four wide on the far turn then closed steadily and just nipped. LUTE'S DIAMOND got outsprinted, had to circle five wide on the far turn and finished willingly. JERSEY BIRD saved ground for three furlongs then made a run inside the winner to loom boldly into the stretch but could not sustain theat bid. LEAD ACTRESS trailed while in the two path to the stretch then could not offer the needed late response. HAMPTONRUN attended the pace outside the winner, was three wide to the stretch but tired in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Lady Ranger
ENTRY.COMMENT: contested pace, responded stretch, got not

ENTRY.NAME: Jersey Bird
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, bid inside, loomed upper stretch, outkicked
